oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Residence of James Winchester, "Cragfont," one mile west of Castalian Springs, Tennessee.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: General James Winchester fought in the Revolution, was a pioneer in the wilderness, a Brigadier General in the War of 1812, a leader in early Tennessee history, and a founder of Memphis.
